<section id="Uninstall_from_Eclipse_Marketplace" remap="TID_13341">
	<sectioninfo>
		<keywordset>
			<keyword>
				JBDS 7.0.0
			</keyword>
		</keywordset>
	</sectioninfo>
	<title>Uninstall JBoss Developer Studio BYOE</title>
	<procedure>
		<title>Uninstall from Eclipse Marketplace</title>
		<step>
			<para>
				Start Eclipse Kepler.
			</para>
		</step>
		<step>
			<para>
				Click <guimenu>Help</guimenu>&rarr;<guimenu>Eclipse Marketplace</guimenu>.
			</para>
		</step>
		<step>
			<para>
				In the <guilabel>Find</guilabel> field of the <guilabel>Search</guilabel> tab, type <command>JBoss Developer Studio</command> and press <keycap>Enter</keycap>.
			</para>
		</step>
		<step>
			<para>
				Locate <application>JBoss Developer Studio (Kepler)</application> and click <guibutton>Uninstall</guibutton>.
			</para>
		</step>
		<step>
			<para>
				Ensure the <guilabel>JBoss Developer Studio (Kepler)</guilabel> check box is selected and click <guibutton>Finish</guibutton>.
			</para>
		</step>
		<step>
			<para>
				Once installing is complete, you are prompted to restart Eclipse. Click <guibutton>Yes</guibutton> to restart immediately and <guibutton>No</guibutton> if you need to save any unsaved changes to open projects. Note that changes do not take effect until Eclipse is restarted.
			</para>
		</step>
	</procedure>
</section>